FBIS3-30904 "dreeu028_d_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 SLOVAKIA Poll Reveals Party Preferences; HZDS Leads AU1002102194 Bratislava SME in Slovak 5 Feb 94 p 1 AU1002102194 Bratislava SME Language: Slovak Article Type:BFN [TA SR report: "Is the Slovak National Party Sinking?"] [Text] According to the FOCUS (Center for Social and Marketing Analysis) agency, in reply to a question on which parties they would vote for if parliamentary elections were held this weekend, respondents answered as follows: Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] (17.2 percent); Party of the Democratic Left (11.4 percent); Christian Democratic Movement (7.1 percent); and Slovak Green Party (5.0 percent). The Slovak National Party (3.8 percent) would come sixth and the Alliance of Democrats of Slovakia, the so-called Knazkoites, would come eighth (2.3 percent). Only 0.4 percent of citizens in Slovakia would vote for the Hungarian Civic Party. More than 20 percent of respondents would not take part in the elections and almost 11 percent had not yet made a decision.
